Git installation and configuration:

#Install the git in linux system by the following command

sudo apt-get install git

#navigate to the directory to which you want to make as local repository directory

#the following command initiates that specific directory as local repository

git init

#add all the files in the directory to git repository

git add *

#commit the files that are selected

git commit -m "First Commit"

#check the status of the files updated

git status

#specifyt your repository URL and it will prompt for username and password of your git account

git remote add origin <url>

#push the files to the git repository

git push -u origin master


